  <instructions>
    <step>For the stovetop method, put the oats and milk in a saucepan and bring to the boil. Lower the heat and simmer, stirring often for 2-3 minutes. Add the mashed banana and simmer for 1-2 minutes more, stirring often.</step>
    <step>For the microwave method, combine the oats and milk in a glass bowl and microwave on high for 1 1/2 minutes. Remove, stir in the banana and microwave for 1 minute.</step>
    <step>Transfer to a serving bowl, sprinkle with cinnamon, if using, and top with a spoonful or so of honey or sugar. Serve immediately, with extra milk if liked and sliced bananas or any other fresh or dried fruit.</step>
  </instructions>
